---
/**
 * context-engineering/0007 · Figure 1 — HERO "Baseline RAG (Lesson 3) — three
 * places it levels up".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0007-pre-retrieval-and-advanced-rag.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers (arw/arwG/arwR/arwM) ONCE in a
 * shared <svg> at the top of <body>. That shared block does not exist in the MDX
 * body, so each figure that needs markers carries its own <defs> with the same
 * ids. ids are scoped to this inline SVG and match the source DOM.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The baseline pipeline upgraded at three points: a pre-retrieval stage, a structured retriever, and a self-correcting loop around the answer."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <!-- baseline row -->
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Baseline RAG (Lesson 3) &mdash; three places it levels up</text
        >

        <!-- Question -->
        <rect x="24" y="40" width="104" height="40" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#111110"
        ></rect><text
            x="76"
            y="64"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">Question</text
        >
        <!-- pre-retrieval (M1) -->
        <rect
            x="160"
            y="40"
            width="120"
            height="40"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect><text
            x="220"
            y="58"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">Pre-retrieval</text
        ><text x="220" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >M1 · fix the query</text
        >
        <!-- retrieval (M2) -->
        <rect
            x="312"
            y="40"
            width="120"
            height="40"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect><text
            x="372"
            y="58"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">Retrieval</text
        ><text x="372" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >M2 · structure it</text
        >
        <!-- LLM -->
        <rect x="464" y="40" width="104" height="40" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#111110"
        ></rect><text
            x="516"
            y="64"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">LLM &rarr; Answer</text
        >

        <line x1="128" y1="60" x2="158" y2="60" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="280" y1="60" x2="310" y2="60" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="432" y1="60" x2="462" y2="60" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- the loop (M3) -->
        <rect
            x="312"
            y="150"
            width="256"
            height="56"
            rx="10"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="440" y="170" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >M3 · agentic / self-correcting loop</text
        >
        <text x="440" y="186" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >grade docs &middot; re-retrieve &middot; critique the draft</text
        >
        <text x="440" y="199" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >retrieval becomes an ACTION, not one step</text
        >
        <!-- loop arrows -->
        <line x1="516" y1="80" x2="516" y2="148" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <line x1="372" y1="148" x2="372" y2="82" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <text x="556" y="118" text-anchor="end" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e"
            >draft</text
        >
        <text x="332" y="118" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e">re-search</text>

        <!-- captions for the three levers -->
        <text x="220" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >recall the question can't buy</text
        >
        <text x="372" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >precision + the right shape</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Three independent upgrades to the same pipeline. <b>M1</b> rewrites the input before it hits the
        index, <b>M2</b> changes what "retrieval" returns, and <b>M3</b> wraps the whole thing in a loop
        that checks its own work. You can adopt one, two, or all three.<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
